// The shipped-content corpus at the SCREEN horizon: the same runs as
// sweeps/shipped-packs.ron, all at 3 000 ticks / 30 observer samples —
// the horizon the search loop screens at (sweeps/search-01.ron and
// successors).
//
// Why this exists (search-01 finding 5, generalized): the 20k corpus
// baseline and a search's 3k screens are not comparable — different
// horizons aggregate different timelines — so the first search could
// only say "no discovered regime beats the corpus" by paying for 20k
// evaluations of every champion, which is hours per bonded regime.
// This sweep gives every shipped pack a row at the screen horizon, so
// screen-fitness comparisons are apples-to-apples and a champion that
// fails to beat the corpus *here* never needs its 20k evaluation at all.
// The 20k baseline remains the exit-criterion authority; this is the
// cheap first gate.
//
//   genesis sweep --spec sweeps/shipped-packs-3k.ron --out <results-dir>
//
// Committed results: docs/research/sweeps/2026-07-14-shipped-packs-3k/
#![enable(implicit_some)]
(
    ticks: 3000,
    every: 100,
    runs: [
        // Control: pure physics, no interactions.
        (name: "physics-only"),
        // Single-mechanism regimes on the default config.
        (name: "diffusion", rules: "packs/diffusion.ron"),
        (name: "hoarders", rules: "packs/hoarders.ron"),
        (name: "chains", rules: "packs/chains.ron"),
        // Echoes needs a world with information in it (see the 20k spec).
        (
            name: "echoes",
            config: "configs/env-gradient.ron",
            rules: "packs/echoes.ron",
        ),
        (name: "churn", rules: "packs/churn.ron"),
        // The two-packs-one-engine pair.
        (name: "actual", rules: "packs/actual.ron"),
        (name: "sandbox", rules: "packs/sandbox.ron"),
        // Environment-gated bonding on its canonical gradient world.
        (
            name: "bands",
            config: "configs/env-gradient.ron",
            rules: "packs/bands.ron",
        ),
        // Selection pressure (already 3k in the 20k spec — same row here).
        (
            name: "sieve",
            config: "configs/sieve.ron",
            rules: "packs/sieve.ron",
        ),
        // Environment-differential selection: the sieve with a raised
        // env-gated information floor where field 0 is high.
        (
            name: "gradient-sieve",
            config: "configs/gradient-sieve.ron",
            rules: "packs/gradient-sieve.ron",
        ),
        // Kitchen sink: env dynamics + LOD + scripted edits/impact/rift.
        (
            name: "full-stack",
            config: "configs/full-stack.ron",
            rules: "packs/bands.ron",
            actions: "scripts/full-stack.ron",
        ),
    ],
)
